===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|god|lang=ang||deity}}, {{etyl|goh}} {{term|got|lang=goh}} (a rank of deity) originally neuter, then changed to masculine to reflect the change in religion to Christianity, both from the {{proto|gem-pro|gudan|lang=en}}, from the {{proto|ine-pro|ǵʰuto-|invoked [one]|lang=en}}, from {{proto|ine-pro|ǵʰewH-|to call, to invoke|lang=en}} or {{proto|ine-pro|ǵʰew-|to pour|lang=en|title=}}. Not related to the word {{term|good|lang=en}}.

